## 🗺️ Task → Agent Call Table (Routing Logic)

Use this table in **STEP 1 — CLASSIFY**. Match the **best-fit agent(s)**; multiple matches are common.

| Domain Signal (keywords, paths, intent) | Agent to Read |
|---------------------------------------|---------------|
| design, Figma, token, color, layout, component, shadcn, UI, screen, a11y, Dashboard, DashboardA | `agents/ux-ui-specialist.md` |
| React, component, hook, TanStack, Zod, form, route, frontend, page, tsx, `frontend-web/` | `agents/frontend-engineer.md` |
| Spring, Kotlin, use case, controller, HATEOAS, endpoint, OpenAPI, module, BFF, `backend/` | `agents/backend-architect.md` |
| schema, migration, Flyway, SQL, index, JPA, entity, table, JSONB, query, database, repository | `agents/database-engineer.md` |
| JWT, Argon2, auth, security, password, authority, FGAC, rate limit, OWASP, token, login, session | `agents/security-engineer.md` |
| mobile, Expo, React Native, NativeWind, push, notification, QR, barcode, iOS, Android, `mobile/` | `agents/mobile-engineer.md` |
| Docker, CI/CD, GitHub Actions, deploy, Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, MinIO, backup, env, ops | `agents/devops-engineer.md` |
| RequestType, workflow, state machine, form_schema, DynamicForm, wizard, transition, solicitação | `agents/workflow-engine-specialist.md` |

### Implicit Cross-Domain Triggers (always load these additionally)

| If the task involves... | Also auto-load |
|------------------------|----------------|
| Any new API endpoint | `security-engineer` + `database-engineer` (if persistence changes) |
| Any new authenticated screen | `security-engineer` + matching UI agent (`ux-ui` + `frontend` or `mobile`) |
| Any new DB table or column | `database-engineer` + `backend-architect` |
| Any solicitação / request feature | `workflow-engine-specialist` + `backend-architect` + `frontend-engineer` |
| Any presença / event / attendance feature | `backend-architect` + `security-engineer` + `database-engineer` + UI agent |
| Project bootstrap / first run | `devops-engineer` + `backend-architect` + `database-engineer` |

### Multi-Domain Orchestration Order

When multiple agents match, execute phases in this **fixed order** (read each agent file before its phase):

```
1. security-engineer     → auth, permissions, rate limits, audit requirements
2. database-engineer     → schema, migrations, indexes
3. workflow-engine-specialist → (if solicitações/workflow involved)
4. backend-architect     → domain, use cases, API, HATEOAS
5. devops-engineer       → (if infra/CI/deploy involved)
6. ux-ui-specialist      → layout, tokens, component spec, states
7. frontend-engineer     → React implementation
8. mobile-engineer       → (if mobile scope included)
```

**Example** — "Implement attendance check-in for events":
```
Read security-engineer → window validation, device binding, rate limits
Read database-engineer → attendance_session schema, UNIQUE constraints
Read backend-architect → ConfirmAttendanceUseCase, canonical endpoints
Read ux-ui-specialist  → AttendanceWidget states (loading/active/expired/confirmed)
Read frontend-engineer → AttendanceWidget + useActions integration
Read mobile-engineer   → QR scanner + PIN input (if mobile in scope)
```

