## ⚠️ Anti-Patterns to AVOID

### Code Smells (Immediate Refactor)
- **Magic Numbers**: Use named constants or enums
- **God Classes**: Split when > 300 lines or > 10 responsibilities
- **Primitive Obsession**: Wrap CPF, Email, GRR in value objects
- **Shotgun Surgery**: If changing 1 requirement touches 5+ files, you broke DRY

### Security Sins (Block in Code Review)
- Hardcoded credentials (even for dev — use `.env`)
- Logging sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII)
- SQL string concatenation (use parameterized queries or JPA)
- Accepting `eval()` or `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without sanitization
- Weak regex for email validation (use library like `email-validator`)

### Performance Killers
- **N+1 Queries**: Use `@EntityGraph` or JOIN FETCH in JPQL
- **Missing Indexes**: Every FK and filter column should have index
- **Unbounded Collections**: Always paginate (`Pageable` in Spring Data)
- **Synchronous I/O in Loop**: Use `@Async`, `CompletableFuture`, or coroutines

---

## 🎯 Success Metrics (How We Measure Quality)

### Code Quality
- Test Coverage: Domain ≥85%, Application ≥70%, Total ≥75%
- Lint Violations: 0 errors (warnings acceptable if justified)
- Cyclomatic Complexity: ≤10 per function (McCabe)
- Duplicated Blocks: <3% (SonarQube)

### Performance (P95)
- API Response: <300ms (list), <100ms (detail)
- Dashboard Load: <1.5s (FCP), <3s (LCP)
- Login: <800ms (including Argon2 verification)
- Outbox Lag: <30s (PENDING → SENT)

### Security
- OWASP Top 10: 0 critical/high findings
- Dependency Vulnerabilities: Patch within 14 days (CVE critical)
- Secrets Leak: 0 (gitleaks enforced)

### User Experience
- Mobile Responsiveness: All screens work on 375px width
- Accessibility: WCAG 2.1 Level AA (aria-labels, focus, contrast)
- Error Recovery: All forms have validation + clear error messages

