## 📞 Escalation & Decision Authority

### Master Agent Can Decide
- Implementation details (class names, file structure within module)
- Library choice **within approved stack** (e.g., date-fns vs dayjs)
- Refactoring for readability (extract method, rename variable)
- Test strategy (unit vs integration for specific case)

### Master Agent MUST Ask User
- Changing tech stack (e.g., replacing Spring with Quarkus)
- Adding new bounded context not in analysis docs
- Modifying API contracts already consumed by frontend
- Changing database schema on tables with data
- Deviating from ADRs (architectural decision records)

### Master Agent MUST Consult Documentation
- **Before**: Creating new RequestType, adding FGAC authority, designing new workflow state
- **Reference**: Sections 3-6 of architectural analysis
- **Verify**: No contradiction with existing ADRs (section 14)

---

## 🔄 Continuous Improvement

This `.cursorrules` file is **living documentation**. Update when:
- New ADR is written (append to section 14 reference)
- Tech stack decision changes (e.g., RabbitMQ is adopted → update Outbox section)
- A new sub-agent is created → add it to the Sub-Agent Directory table
- Team convention evolves (e.g., prefer `AsyncResult<T>` over `CompletableFuture<T>`)

**Last Updated**: 2026-06-07 (v1.2 — Mandatory auto-delegation to specialist agents)

---

## 🙏 Philosophy

> "The best architecture is the one you don't have to refactor after the MVP."

We achieve this through:
- **Contracts First** (OpenAPI before code)
- **Tokens First** (Figma Variables before hardcoded styles)
- **Schema First** (Flyway migrations before JPA entities)
- **Tests First** (TDD for domain, test-after for infra)

**Result**: The walking skeleton (login → dashboard) built in 15 days uses the **same structure** as the final product with all 46 routes. We **add folders**, never **move code**.

---

## 🗂️ Agent Ecosystem Quick Reference

```
agents/
  ux-ui-specialist.md          → Figma, design tokens, shadcn/ui, DashboardA blueprint
  frontend-engineer.md         → React, TypeScript, TanStack Query, HATEOAS useActions
  backend-architect.md         → Kotlin, Spring Boot, Clean Architecture, HATEOAS assemblers
  database-engineer.md         → PostgreSQL, Flyway, JPA, indexes, JSONB
  security-engineer.md         → JWT, Argon2id, FGAC, Spring Security, OWASP
  mobile-engineer.md           → React Native, Expo, NativeWind, push, QR, Keychain
  devops-engineer.md           → Docker, GitHub Actions, Prometheus, Grafana, MinIO
  workflow-engine-specialist.md → RequestType, WorkflowDefinition, DynamicForm, 19 types
```

**Auto-delegation (default)**: Master reads matching agent files from Call Table before acting.  
**Manual override**: `@agents/<filename>.md` makes that agent primary for its domain; others still auto-load for cross-cutting work.

